description: Official X-Files tie-in magazine published by Manga Entertainment in the U.K. Along side articles and features on the show, it also reprinted the Topps' X-Files comics in serialised format. From issue #19 Titan Magazines took over publication, continuing the original format and numbering through to at least #35. With Topps material running out, and with MVP Media starting a license to print an X-Files Official Magazine in the USA, in 1998 Titan ended this title, and launched a new title, X-Files The Official Magazine, reprinting the MVP title and featuring no comic strip material.
name: X-Files

deck: Promotional book available via Cadburys, and tied to the Goodies TV show.
description: Produced by IPC for confectionary company Cadbury Limited, the Goodies Fun Books featured reprinted Goodies strips originally published in Cor!!, alongside new features such as puzzles. Though published simultaneously, unnumbered, and with identical indicia and titles, the two Goodies Fun Books had differing contents, with one aimed at younger readers and featuring new, less complicated comic strips alongside fewer Cor!! reprints. Both books were promotional items, and could available directly from Cadburys upon sending in a specified number of wrappers taken from Cadbury chocolates or sweets.
name: The Goodies Fun Book

description:
The fourth ongoing-series of Captain Marvel. The first female Captain Marvel ongoing, starring Carol Danvers. The series is famous for staring the first appearance of Kamala Khan (the new Ms. Marvel) in issue 14. The series lasted for 17 issues and was almost directly continued in Captain Marvel Volume 5.

Written by Kelly Sue DeConnick (with co-writer Christopher Sebela for issues 7-8 and 10-12).

Dexter Soy drew and colored issues 1-4 and 7-8;

Emma Rios drew issues 5-6; and Filipe Andrade drew issues 9-12. Jordie Bellaire colored issues 5-6 and 9-12.

Collected Editions

  • Vol. 1: In Pursuit of Flight (#1-6)
  • Captain Marvel: Earth's Mightiest Hero Volume 1 (#1-12)
  • Guardians of the Galaxy: Guardians Disassembled (#1)
  • Heroes of Power: The Women of Marvel - All-New Marvel Treasury Edition (#1)
  • Vol. 2: Down (#7-11)
  • Avengers: The Enemy Within (#13-14, #17)
  • Captain Marvel: Earth's Mightiest Hero Volume 2 (#13-17)
  • Infinity Companion (#15-16)
  • Captain Marvel & The Carol Corps: Warzones! (#17)

Issue's #13-17 have been translated into Spanish.
name: Captain Marvel

description: Written and published by Dean Wilkinson, who also created the short lived Acne, and with art by Mervyn Johnston and Lee Healey, Fizog was an attempt to produce an anarchic comic for kids somewhat like Viz or Oink! Feature characters included the incredibly lazy boy Billy Idle, the stretching girl Bendy Wendy, Marge Ick's Tricks (about a young magician whose spells never go quite as intended) and alien visitor to Earth Al Eenbeeng. It only lasted three issues.
name: Fizog
